author: Fish Eyes
text:
Both are equally fine tbh. It's just that Green Rushia has a more inspired and unique design for me compared to Pink Rushia whose design elements feels a bit more "borrowed" and less distinct. Give me a black silhouette of Green Rushia in any pose, I'll be able to identify it's her, but give me a black silhouette of Pink Rushia, I might mistake her for other characters. It isn't necessarily bad, it's just that the green variant is more iconic for Rushia, pink variant at a glance at times just feels like another whole new character.

But, come on! You've got gothic lolita dress, stockings, red eyes, twin tail pink hair, sometimes glasses, loli, and flat all in one! If Kaguya-sama taught me anything, we've got a perfect marriage right here. There's no way Pink Rushia's any less cute.
